## Suggested README Section: AI-Assisted Project Work

This project uses the Alubys AI Development System for structured AI-assisted project work.

Key files:

- `AGENTS.md` — canonical instructions for AI agents
- `CLAUDE.md` — Claude handoff that points to `AGENTS.md`
- `MASTER_SYSTEM_PROMPT.md` — operating protocol for AI sessions
- `.agent/memory/active-context.md` — current project state
- `.agent/tasks/in-progress.md` — active work
- `.agent/tasks/roadmap.md` — project direction
- `.agent/memory/lessons-learned.md` — durable lessons and rules
- `.agent/memory/decisions.md` — architecture, operating, and project decisions already made

To start an AI session:

1. Open your AI assistant
2. Say: "Follow `AGENTS.md`, read the startup files, and tell me where we are."

Fallback: if the AI cannot read project files, paste `MASTER_SYSTEM_PROMPT.md`, relevant startup files, and any setup or mode prompt manually.

To end an AI session:

1. Say: "Run the closeout protocol."
2. Confirm `.agent/memory/active-context.md`, `.agent/memory/changelog.md`, and `.agent/tasks/in-progress.md` are current.
3. Confirm the next session can resume from the startup files alone.

