## Suggested README Section: Agent Memory

Commit `.agent/` by default, including `.agent/sessions/`. The `.agent/` directory is project memory; committing it preserves context across machines, contributors, and AI systems.

Do not commit real secret values. Reference secrets by name only, such as `DATABASE_URL` or `OPENAI_API_KEY`.

Real values belong in:

- Environment variables
- A password manager
- `.agent/secrets.local.md`

`.agent/secrets.local.md` is ignored by `.agent/.gitignore`.

